Nov 3, 2025
KZ One is a scalping strategy developed for M1 and M5 timeframes. It is designed to help traders study and practice short-term market behavior by using structured zones to highlight potential entry and exit areas. The strategy allows customization of Risk (USD) and Take Profit (R multiple) parameters for flexible trade management. Additional tools include ATR-based filters to skip low-volatility conditions and a Pre-Alert Lead (bars) option that notifies users ahead of possible setups. KZ One is intended for educational and analytical purposes, promoting disciplined and consistent trading practice.
Nov 3, 2025
Release Notes
Added on-chart trade display comments for better visualization.
Now each trade shows detailed information directly on the chart:

BUY trades: BUY @<price> tp=<price> sl=<price>

SELL trades: SELL @@<price> tp=<price> sl=<price>

Exit trades: Close @<price>
This update improves clarity for visual training, backtesting review, and educational use inside the KZ One Scalping Training Strategy.
